The new world is in sight.

00:45:24.271 --> 00:45:33.113 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Just keep on holding tight.
I’ll help you win this fight.’

00:45:34.481 --> 00:45:39.186 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What a beautiful song
and a beautiful reminder!

00:45:39.186 --> 00:45:43.424 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah does help us
to win our “fight of the faith.”

00:45:43.424 --> 00:45:45.426 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In what ways?

00:45:45.426 --> 00:45:47.694 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As we saw in the video, he helps us

00:45:47.694 --> 00:45:50.197 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
through our family and fellow worshippers,

00:45:50.197 --> 00:45:54.301 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
through the ministry,
and through his Word, the Bible.

00:45:54.301 --> 00:45:57.738 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Preserving God’s Word and his personal name

00:45:57.738 --> 00:46:01.008 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
has been a fierce fight over many centuries

00:46:01.008 --> 00:46:03.310 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—a fight that’s being won.

00:46:03.310 --> 00:46:08.248 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is the subject of the Bible Museum
at world headquarters in Warwick, New York.

00:46:08.248 --> 00:46:11.018 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s take a brief tour.

00:46:11.018 --> 00:46:15.289 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible is a modern-day treasure.

00:46:15.289 --> 00:46:19.493 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It reveals the satisfying truth about God,

00:46:19.493 --> 00:46:22.396 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
life, and our hope for the future.

00:46:22.396 --> 00:46:26.667 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What’s more,
it contains another priceless treasure

00:46:26.667 --> 00:46:30.904 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—God’s personal name, Jehovah.

00:46:30.904 --> 00:46:34.675 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
How Jehovah preserved his name
in the Holy Scriptures,

00:46:34.675 --> 00:46:39.446 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
against all attempts to remove it,
is a fascinating story.

00:46:39.446 --> 00:46:42.349 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And it’s told here in the Bible Museum

00:46:42.349 --> 00:46:45.085 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
at world headquarters in Warwick.

00:46:45.085 --> 00:46:47.321 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s take the tour.

00:46:47.321 --> 00:46:49.656 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At the museum’s entry,

00:46:49.656 --> 00:46:53.093 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the divine name is shown in various languages

00:46:53.093 --> 00:46:57.764 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a total of 7,216 times.

00:46:57.764 --> 00:46:59.967 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
That’s how many times it appears

00:46:59.967 --> 00:47:03.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the New World Translation
of the Holy Scriptures.

00:47:03.470 --> 00:47:08.141 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah always made his name known,
even to the very first humans.

00:47:08.141 --> 00:47:12.045 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When Cain was born,
Eve declared:

00:47:12.045 --> 00:47:14.515 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I have produced a male child

00:47:14.515 --> 00:47:17.217 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with the help of Jehovah.”

00:47:17.217 --> 00:47:19.353 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
After that time,

00:47:19.353 --> 00:47:22.689 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
people knew and used God’s name.

00:47:22.689 --> 00:47:27.361 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The oldest example
of the divine name in Hebrew letters

00:47:27.361 --> 00:47:32.366 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is on the Moabite Stone
from the ninth century B.C.E.

00:47:32.366 --> 00:47:36.503 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Moabite King Mesha
boasted against Israel:

00:47:36.503 --> 00:47:39.973 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“I took from it the vessels of Jehovah,

00:47:39.973 --> 00:47:43.010 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and offered them before Chemosh.”

00:47:43.010 --> 00:47:46.647 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
There’s also evidence that in ancient times

00:47:46.647 --> 00:47:50.417 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God’s name was used in everyday life.

00:47:50.417 --> 00:47:54.254 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This silver scroll
from the seventh century B.C.E.

00:47:54.254 --> 00:47:56.757 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is the earliest known inscription

00:47:56.757 --> 00:47:59.927 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of a Bible text containing God’s name.

00:47:59.927 --> 00:48:01.261 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It reads:

00:48:01.261 --> 00:48:04.731 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“May Jehovah bless you and keep you.

00:48:04.731 --> 00:48:07.935 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
May Jehovah make his face to shine on you.”

00:48:07.935 --> 00:48:10.671 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Most important, God’s name

00:48:10.671 --> 00:48:13.574 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was in ancient copies of the Bible text.

00:48:13.574 --> 00:48:15.943 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Fouad Papyrus

00:48:15.943 --> 00:48:18.712 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the first century B.C.E.

00:48:18.712 --> 00:48:21.715 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is a fragment of the Greek Septuagint,

00:48:21.715 --> 00:48:23.717 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the first known translation

00:48:23.717 --> 00:48:25.919 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the Hebrew Scriptures into Greek.

00:48:27.287 --> 00:48:30.891 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here’s Deuteronomy 32:3:

00:48:30.891 --> 00:48:34.194 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“For I will declare the name of Jehovah.”

00:48:35.362 --> 00:48:37.531 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Although the text is in Greek,

00:48:37.531 --> 00:48:40.567 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the divine name is written in Hebrew.

00:48:40.567 --> 00:48:42.569 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Greek-speaking Jews

00:48:42.569 --> 00:48:45.739 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in Jesus’ day used the Septuagint.

00:48:45.739 --> 00:48:49.476 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So when Jesus read and taught
from the Scriptures,

00:48:49.476 --> 00:48:51.578 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
people heard him use the divine name.

00:48:53.380 --> 00:48:57.150 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sadly, though,
by the third century C.E.,

00:48:57.150 --> 00:49:00.454 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God’s name was removed
from the Septuagint

00:49:00.454 --> 00:49:02.656 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and replaced with the title “Lord.”

00:49:02.656 --> 00:49:04.358 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As an example,

00:49:04.358 --> 00:49:06.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Vatican Codex

00:49:06.460 --> 00:49:10.130 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the fourth century C.E.
includes the text

00:49:10.130 --> 00:49:14.001 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the Greek Septuagint
but omits God’s name.

00:49:14.001 --> 00:49:18.138 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Deuteronomy 32:3 here reads:

00:49:18.138 --> 00:49:21.174 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“For I will declare the name of the LORD.”

00:49:21.174 --> 00:49:22.843 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But Jehovah

00:49:22.843 --> 00:49:25.946 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
wouldn’t allow his name to be lost.

00:49:25.946 --> 00:49:29.116 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was never removed
from Hebrew copies of the Bible.

00:49:29.116 --> 00:49:31.118 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Aleppo Codex

00:49:31.118 --> 00:49:34.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was copied by Jewish scribes

00:49:34.154 --> 00:49:36.356 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
around the year 930 C.E.

00:49:36.356 --> 00:49:38.125 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The same verse,

00:49:38.125 --> 00:49:42.629 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Deuteronomy 32:3, says in Hebrew:

00:49:42.629 --> 00:49:46.099 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
“For I will declare the name of Jehovah.”

00:49:46.099 --> 00:49:48.101 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Still,

00:49:48.101 --> 00:49:51.304 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for centuries, most people didn’t have

00:49:51.304 --> 00:49:53.640 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a Bible in their own language,

00:49:53.640 --> 00:49:56.143 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
nor one that contained God’s name.

00:49:57.444 --> 00:49:59.446 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Latin Vulgate,

00:49:59.446 --> 00:50:02.482 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
translated around 405 C.E.,

00:50:02.482 --> 00:50:04.518 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
omitted the divine name.

00:50:04.518 --> 00:50:07.254 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It became the official translation

00:50:07.254 --> 00:50:11.491 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the Catholic Church for over 1,000 years.

00:50:11.491 --> 00:50:14.628 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But a new technology triggered events

00:50:14.628 --> 00:50:18.365 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that would soon make
the Bible widely available

00:50:18.365 --> 00:50:20.367 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and in fresh translations

00:50:20.367 --> 00:50:23.837 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that returned God’s name
to its rightful place.

00:50:23.837 --> 00:50:28.341 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
About 1453, 
Johannes Gutenberg

00:50:28.341 --> 00:50:31.144 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
produced an important edition
of the Latin Vulgate.

00:50:31.144 --> 00:50:33.146 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was the first Bible 

00:50:33.146 --> 00:50:35.582 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
printed using movable type.

00:50:36.850 --> 00:50:41.154 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is an original page
from a Gutenberg Bible.

00:50:41.154 --> 00:50:45.258 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
While only some 180 Bibles were made,

00:50:45.258 --> 00:50:49.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
his invention sparked a printing revolution.

00:50:49.229 --> 00:50:53.834 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Just 20 years later,
Anton Koberger was printing

00:50:53.834 --> 00:50:56.770 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
up to 1,000 Bibles per run,

00:50:56.770 --> 00:51:00.440 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
making it the first mass-produced Bible.

00:51:00.440 --> 00:51:03.376 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
On display is an original copy

00:51:03.376 --> 00:51:05.378 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the second edition

00:51:05.378 --> 00:51:09.883 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of Koberger’s Latin Bible from 1477.

00:51:09.883 --> 00:51:12.953 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Then, in the early 1500’s,

00:51:12.953 --> 00:51:15.589 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Bible scholars took a renewed interest

00:51:15.589 --> 00:51:18.191 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the original Bible languages.

00:51:18.191 --> 00:51:20.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
For the very first time,

00:51:20.460 --> 00:51:24.831 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the original-language Hebrew
and Greek Scriptures were printed together.

00:51:25.799 --> 00:51:28.435 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is the Complutensian Polyglot,

00:51:28.435 --> 00:51:32.105 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
printed between 1514 and 1517.

00:51:33.140 --> 00:51:34.975 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
A polyglot is a book

00:51:34.975 --> 00:51:38.712 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with text in several languages
arranged in columns.

00:51:38.712 --> 00:51:41.381 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In the Complutensian Polyglot,

00:51:41.381 --> 00:51:43.984 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Bible text appears in Latin,

00:51:43.984 --> 00:51:47.788 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hebrew, Aramaic, and Greek.

00:51:47.788 --> 00:51:51.291 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Comparing the Hebrew text with the Latin,

00:51:51.291 --> 00:51:53.627 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
scholars could see where God’s name

00:51:53.627 --> 00:51:57.731 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
had been replaced
in the Latin Vulgate with “LORD.”

00:51:59.132 --> 00:52:03.236 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But would seeing the divine name
in the original Hebrew text

00:52:03.236 --> 00:52:05.972 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
lead Bible translators to restore

00:52:05.972 --> 00:52:08.508 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God’s name in their translations?

00:52:08.508 --> 00:52:11.244 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Indeed, some did!

00:52:11.244 --> 00:52:13.847 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In 1551,

00:52:13.847 --> 00:52:16.316 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Sebastian Castellio published

00:52:16.316 --> 00:52:19.519 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
his fresh Latin translation of the Bible.

00:52:19.519 --> 00:52:21.822 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He appears to be the first

00:52:21.822 --> 00:52:24.024 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to use God’s name consistently

00:52:24.024 --> 00:52:25.692 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in a Latin translation

00:52:25.692 --> 00:52:27.694 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the Hebrew Scriptures.

00:52:27.694 --> 00:52:30.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Translations into other languages

00:52:30.530 --> 00:52:32.532 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
were also using God’s name.

00:52:32.532 --> 00:52:36.203 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In 1530, William Tyndale

00:52:36.203 --> 00:52:38.538 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
published his English translation

00:52:38.538 --> 00:52:40.607 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of Genesis through Deuteronomy.

00:52:40.607 --> 00:52:42.609 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It was the first time

00:52:42.609 --> 00:52:44.611 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that the divine name appeared

00:52:44.611 --> 00:52:46.847 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in any English Bible.

00:52:46.847 --> 00:52:49.649 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The popular Reina-Valera Spanish Bible

00:52:49.649 --> 00:52:52.352 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was published in 1602.

00:52:52.352 --> 00:52:54.487 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It contains the divine name

00:52:54.487 --> 00:52:56.823 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
throughout the Hebrew Scriptures.

00:52:58.458 --> 00:53:02.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is a rare original first edition

00:53:02.229 --> 00:53:04.564 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the English King James Version

00:53:04.564 --> 00:53:08.201 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the Bible, published in 1611.

00:53:08.201 --> 00:53:10.237 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It uses the name Jehovah

00:53:10.237 --> 00:53:12.305 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in just four passages.

00:53:12.305 --> 00:53:15.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Still, the King James Version became

00:53:15.642 --> 00:53:18.411 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the most widely printed book in the world.

00:53:18.411 --> 00:53:20.680 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Some 200 years later,

00:53:20.680 --> 00:53:22.682 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Benjamin Boothroyd,

00:53:22.682 --> 00:53:25.018 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
a minister and Hebrew scholar,

00:53:25.018 --> 00:53:28.255 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
set out to revise the King James Version.

00:53:28.255 --> 00:53:31.324 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
His 1817 translation

00:53:31.324 --> 00:53:33.360 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was the first English Bible

00:53:33.360 --> 00:53:35.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to use the divine name throughout

00:53:35.729 --> 00:53:37.831 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Hebrew Scriptures.

00:53:37.831 --> 00:53:40.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Meanwhile, church missionaries

00:53:40.267 --> 00:53:43.603 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
were taking the Bible to new lands.

00:53:43.603 --> 00:53:47.908 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But without the divine name,
people couldn’t distinguish

00:53:47.908 --> 00:53:50.944 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the God of the Bible
from their own false gods.

00:53:50.944 --> 00:53:53.380 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
So Bible translations

00:53:53.380 --> 00:53:55.715 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
in many languages of Asia,

00:53:55.715 --> 00:53:58.051 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Africa, the Pacific islands,

00:53:58.051 --> 00:54:00.720 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
and the Americas included God’s name.

00:54:02.088 --> 00:54:05.525 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Chinese Delegate’s Version from 1854

00:54:05.525 --> 00:54:08.295 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
is an example of a missionary Bible

00:54:08.295 --> 00:54:10.530 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that uses God’s name throughout

00:54:10.530 --> 00:54:12.866 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Hebrew Scriptures.

00:54:12.866 --> 00:54:14.868 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Still, there was

00:54:14.868 --> 00:54:17.470 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
one more place where God’s name

00:54:17.470 --> 00:54:20.140 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was not yet restored

00:54:20.140 --> 00:54:22.676 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—the Christian Greek Scriptures.

00:54:22.676 --> 00:54:25.612 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is the Nuremberg Polyglot,

00:54:25.612 --> 00:54:29.649 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
published by Elias Hutter in 1599.

00:54:29.649 --> 00:54:32.385 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It contains the Christian Greek Scriptures

00:54:32.385 --> 00:54:35.155 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in 12 languages, including Hebrew.

00:54:36.256 --> 00:54:37.757 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Here,

00:54:37.757 --> 00:54:42.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
John’s Gospel
quotes Psalm 118:26:

00:54:42.562 --> 00:54:47.100 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Blessed is the one who comes
in Jehovah’s name.”

00:54:47.100 --> 00:54:49.970 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In his Hebrew translation of the Gospel,

00:54:49.970 --> 00:54:53.273 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Hutter preserved the divine name
in the quotation

00:54:53.273 --> 00:54:54.841 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from Psalms.

00:54:54.841 --> 00:54:59.012 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He did this in many other places
in the Greek Scriptures.

00:54:59.012 --> 00:55:01.715 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Translators had a precedent

00:55:01.715 --> 00:55:05.919 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to use God’s name
in the Christian Greek Scriptures

00:55:05.919 --> 00:55:09.990 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
where the name appeared
in verses quoted from the Hebrew Scriptures.

00:55:09.990 --> 00:55:13.827 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This is the 1864 sixth edition

00:55:13.827 --> 00:55:16.029 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
New Testament translation

00:55:16.029 --> 00:55:18.331 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by Herman Heinfetter.

00:55:18.331 --> 00:55:20.700 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
It’s likely the first published

00:55:20.700 --> 00:55:23.303 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
English Bible to use God’s name

00:55:23.303 --> 00:55:25.839 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in more than 100 places

00:55:25.839 --> 00:55:27.841 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
in the Christian Greek Scriptures.

00:55:29.209 --> 00:55:32.779 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The New World Translation
of the Holy Scriptures

00:55:32.779 --> 00:55:37.283 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
was first published between 1950 and 1960.

00:55:37.283 --> 00:55:39.853 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Its translators benefited

00:55:39.853 --> 00:55:42.989 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
from the scholarly work of those before them

00:55:42.989 --> 00:55:47.961 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who had chosen to preserve God’s name
in their Bible translations.

00:55:47.961 --> 00:55:51.297 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Today, the New World Translation

00:55:51.297 --> 00:55:53.333 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
is available in whole or in part

00:55:53.333 --> 00:55:56.169 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
in over 170 languages.

00:55:57.570 --> 00:55:59.572 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
God’s name, Jehovah,

00:55:59.572 --> 00:56:03.009 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
belongs in the Holy Scriptures he inspired.

00:56:04.844 --> 00:56:08.348 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This gallery holds just a small part

00:56:08.348 --> 00:56:13.319 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of the overwhelming evidence to this fact.

00:56:13.319 --> 00:56:17.624 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible is a precious gift from God,
teaching us

00:56:17.624 --> 00:56:20.760 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
about his works, his qualities,

00:56:20.760 --> 00:56:22.762 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and his loving purpose

00:56:22.762 --> 00:56:24.764 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
for humankind.

00:56:24.764 --> 00:56:27.400 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
He invites each of us to read it,

00:56:27.400 --> 00:56:30.737 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to draw close to him, and to know him

00:56:30.737 --> 00:56:34.441 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by his most holy name, Jehovah.

00:56:35.742 --> 00:56:37.777 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our program has focused

00:56:37.777 --> 00:56:41.481 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
on “perfecting holiness in God’s fear.”

00:56:41.481 --> 00:56:45.852 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
“Perfecting holiness” may sound out of reach,

00:56:45.852 --> 00:56:49.522 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
but remember, it’s a continuous process.

00:56:49.522 --> 00:56:52.325 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We saw this with those young men in Italy

00:56:52.325 --> 00:56:56.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
who left behind
their violent and immoral ways.

00:56:56.229 --> 00:56:58.865 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
And with Jane, Yusuke, and Yutaka,

00:56:58.865 --> 00:57:02.402 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we saw experienced Christians who found ways 

00:57:02.402 --> 00:57:05.171 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to grow as spiritual people.

00:57:05.171 --> 00:57:07.907 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We learned how to make
our speech more upbuilding

00:57:07.907 --> 00:57:11.811 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
by examining our motives and associations.

00:57:13.146 --> 00:57:15.248 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Petter Heinrichs’ experience demonstrates

00:57:15.248 --> 00:57:19.052 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that it’s possible
to return to Jehovah with His help.

00:57:19.052 --> 00:57:21.821 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Finally, our music video reminds us

00:57:21.821 --> 00:57:23.890 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that despite the unique pressures

00:57:23.890 --> 00:57:26.559 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
our young people face,

00:57:26.559 --> 00:57:28.595 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
they’re winning the fight.

00:57:28.595 --> 00:57:30.897 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
We close with a visit

00:57:30.897 --> 00:57:35.301 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to our brothers and sisters in Puerto Rico.

00:57:35.301 --> 00:57:40.306 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Secluded beaches, lush valleys, mountains

00:57:40.306 --> 00:57:42.642 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—this beautiful island is home

00:57:42.642 --> 00:57:45.078 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to more than 3 million inhabitants

00:57:45.078 --> 00:57:49.082 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and nearly 24,000 Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:57:49.082 --> 00:57:53.520 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
But its location in the Caribbean
puts Puerto Rico in the path

00:57:53.520 --> 00:57:56.422 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of tropical storms and hurricanes.

00:57:56.422 --> 00:58:00.460 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One of the most powerful ever,
Hurricane Maria,

00:58:00.460 --> 00:58:02.495 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
struck two years ago.

00:58:02.495 --> 00:58:06.032 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Lives were lost, and homes were destroyed.

00:58:06.032 --> 00:58:09.669 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The entire island
lost electricity for months.

00:58:09.669 --> 00:58:11.804 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
To help with relief efforts,

00:58:11.804 --> 00:58:14.674 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
thousands of brothers and sisters
from Puerto Rico

00:58:14.674 --> 00:58:18.778 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and from across the United States
branch territory volunteered.

00:58:18.778 --> 00:58:20.813 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
They repaired and rebuilt

00:58:20.813 --> 00:58:25.151 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
106 Kingdom Halls, 2 Assembly Halls,

00:58:25.151 --> 00:58:29.022 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and more than 800 homes of our brothers.

00:58:30.123 --> 00:58:34.327 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Barahona Congregation,
located in the middle of the island,

00:58:34.327 --> 00:58:38.464 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was enjoying their circuit overseer visit
when the hurricane hit.

00:58:38.464 --> 00:58:41.367 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The body of elders and the circuit overseer

00:58:41.367 --> 00:58:43.937 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
immediately organized and reached out

00:58:43.937 --> 00:58:46.072 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
to everyone in the congregation.

00:58:46.072 --> 00:58:48.408 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Despite the devastation,

00:58:48.408 --> 00:58:52.278 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Sunday meeting took place as scheduled.

00:58:53.379 --> 00:58:57.483 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
In fact, despite dealing
with challenging conditions for many months,

00:58:57.483 --> 00:59:01.387 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the congregation
didn’t cancel a single meeting.

00:59:01.387 --> 00:59:04.123 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Within a few days of Hurricane Maria,

00:59:04.123 --> 00:59:06.659 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the organized preaching work resumed

00:59:06.659 --> 00:59:09.162 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and our brothers were back in the field.

00:59:09.162 --> 00:59:12.699 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The response has been encouraging.

00:59:12.699 --> 00:59:16.402 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Fifty Bible studies are now being conducted.

00:59:17.737 --> 00:59:22.375 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The 117 publishers
in the Barahona Congregation

00:59:22.375 --> 00:59:26.746 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
send you
their warm Christian love and greetings.

00:59:26.746 --> 00:59:30.450 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:59:30.450 --> 00:59:33.686 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

